      "content": "Meritocracy advocates argue that success should be based on individual effort and talent, not on wealth redistribution. They believe that providing equal opportunities allows everyone to succeed based on their merits. However, this perspective overlooks the structural barriers that have historically disadvantaged certain racial groups. Wealth redistribution doesn't undermine meritocracy; it addresses the unequal starting points that prevent true equality of opportunity. By leveling the playing field, we ensure that everyone has a fair chance to succeed, which ultimately strengthens the meritocratic system. This approach recognizes that true meritocracy can only exist when all individuals have access to the same resources and opportunities.",
